cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.NE 

The paper discusses event-triggered control and estimation, which are commonly used in the field of control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed concept of event-triggered learning also involves adapting to changing dynamics, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper uses statistical analysis and concentration inequalities, which are techniques commonly used in the field of neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE).
